><A HREF="gc.htm"> Of God and His Creatures</a><hr><p>
Fornication is said to be 'simple,' when neither
of the parties is married. -- There is plain speaking in
this chapter, but it contains "a godly and wholesome
doctrine, and necessary for our times." There would
be less sin, if there were a little more plain speaking
to persons under temptation.


